		"name": "Jenkins Job Trigger API",
		"description": "# Jenkins Job Trigger API Collection\n\nThis collection contains API endpoints for triggering Jenkins CI/CD pipeline builds with custom parameters.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe laTrigger iOS application uses these endpoints to interact with Jenkins servers to trigger builds, check job status, and manage CI/CD workflows.\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll endpoints require **Basic Authentication**. You need to provide:\n- **Username**: Your Jenkins username\n- **Password**: Your Jenkins API token (not your password)\n\n## Getting Your Jenkins API Token\n\n1. Log in to Jenkins\n2. Click on your username in the top-right corner\n3. Click \"Configure\" in the left sidebar\n4. Under \"API Token\", click \"Add new Token\"\n5. Give it a name and click \"Generate\"\n6. Copy the token and store it securely\n\n## Environment Variables\n\nThis collection uses the following environment variables:\n- `jenkins_base_url`: Base URL of your Jenkins server\n- `jenkins_username`: Your Jenkins username\n- `jenkins_api_token`: Your Jenkins API token\n- `build_token`: Build trigger token configured in Jenkins job\n- `job_path`: Path to the Jenkins job\n\n## Security Notes\n\n⚠️ **Never commit credentials to version control**\n\n- Store credentials in environment variables\n- Use HTTPS in production\n- Rotate API tokens regularly",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
